### Git basic tutorial by Matt Piajnowski ###

# Basic
git init - Create empty local repository
git remote add origin [url] - Add new remote
git add . - Update local idex repository
git commit -m"[commit comment]" - Add commit comment
git push - Push local repository to remote server

# Branch
git branch [branch name] - Create new branch
git checkout [branch name] - Switch branch
git merge [branch name] - Merge branch
git branch -D [branch name] - Remove local branch
git push --delete [remote name] [branch name] - Remove remote branch

# Commit
git reset --hard [HEAD - e.g origin/master] - Remove a commit before pushed:
git reset --hard [commit key] && git push -f - Remove pushed commit
git reset --soft [commit key] && git commit -m "[new comment]" && git push -f - Change commit comment:

# Other
git status - Local repository status
git remote -v - Remote list
git rebase - Repository synchronization with remote
git remote set-url origin [new remote url] - Edit remotes
git fetch origin && git pull [remote branch name] - Synchronize local branch with remote branch

